## üöÄ Overview

The project is divided into three main operational frameworks:

### 1. Periodic Orbits in the 3D CRTBP
* [cite_start]**Objective**: Find and analyze periodic Halo orbits in the 3D Earth-Moon Circular Restricted Three-Body Problem (CRTBP)[cite: 6, 22].
* **Methods**: 
  * [cite_start]Calculation of the 5 Lagrange points with high accuracy[cite: 11].
  * [cite_start]Implementation of a differential correction scheme utilizing the State Transition Matrix (STM) to enforce perpendicular plane crossings[cite: 23, 24].
  * [cite_start]Numerical continuation to compute families of Halo orbits (ranging from Jacobi Constant C = 3.09 to C = 3.04)[cite: 22, 26].

### 2. Impulsive Guidance (Earth-Moon Transfer)
* [cite_start]**Objective**: Design an optimal two-impulse Earth-Moon transfer[cite: 270].
* **Methods**:
  * [cite_start]Initial propagation using the 2D Planar Bicircular Restricted Four-Body Problem (PBRFBP)[cite: 309].
  * [cite_start]Trajectory optimization applying both Simple Shooting and Multiple Shooting (N = 4 nodes) methods to minimize Delta-V[cite: 278, 281].
  * [cite_start]Real-world validation: Transformation to the Earth-centered inertial frame (ECLIPJ2000) and full N-body propagation using NASA SPICE kernels[cite: 282, 295, 311].

### 3. Continuous Guidance (Low-Thrust Orbit Raising)
* [cite_start]**Objective**: Design an optimal low-thrust maneuver to raise an orbit from 800 km to 1000 km while minimizing collision risk in a high-density spatial debris environment[cite: 736, 737, 738].
* **Methods**:
  * [cite_start]Application of the Pontryagin Maximum Principle (PMP) to formulate the optimal control problem[cite: 748, 863].
  * [cite_start]Resolution of the Zero-Finding problem for the costates and final time using nonlinear root-finding[cite: 876, 877].
  * [cite_start]Numerical continuation applied to evaluate the transfer efficiency under a reduced thrust scenario (from T_max = 3.000 N to 2.860 N)[cite: 758, 902, 987].

